The paper deals with the problem of detecting forgeries in images and videos using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of generalization in forgery detection, which is a common problem in machine learning, and proposes a novel approach to address it. This makes it relevant to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
